c edu updates here here U S  Fulbright Clinton Fellowship U S  Fulbright Clinton Fellowship Fulbright Public Policy Fellowships  through the U S  State Department provides for international work experience at a predetermined location  Student apply at large for this opportunity in the early spring  but please contact the Fellowships Coordinator who has much more information and literature on this award U S  Fulbright Hays Dissertation Fellowship U S  Fulbright Hays Dissertation Fellowship The Fulbright Hays Doctoral Dissertation Research Abroad  DDRA  Fellowship Program provides opportunities for full time dissertation research abroad in modern foreign languages and area studies  Students may request funding for a period of no fewer than six months and no more than    months  Funds support travel expenses to and from the residence of the fellow and the country or countries of research  maintenance and dependents s  allowances based on the location of research for the fellow and his or her dependent s   an allowance for research related expenses overseas  and health and accident insurance premiums  Applicants should plan to have a teaching career in the U S  after completion of the doctorate  The campus deadline is June           the brochure distillation of the FOA can be found here Cf  the brochure Boren Fellowship for International Study Boren Fellowship for International Study  in areas related to U S  National Security  broadly defined  Fellowships provide up to         for overseas study and immersion  minimum    weeks and maximum one year overseas  Preference is given to proposals for    months in duration for linguistic and cultural immersion      months for applicants in the STEM fileds  In exchange for funding  Boren Fellows commit to working in the federal government for at least one year after graduation  Here are some some of the possible federal agencies possible federal agencies Graduate students apply for this fellowship through the Boren Embark porta